<paragraph blockId="5.[151,499,691,751]" box="[151,425,726,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,229,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[215,229,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, E, I, M; 
<number box="[358,372,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
A–I)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,1252,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" box="[151,1252,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Etymology.</emphasis>
This specific epithet is derived from the Greek word “chrōma”, which means “color”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="270" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,834,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[682,795,835,858]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Hilavrita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxeta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[682,795,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">H. saxeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[809,906,834,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[809,906,834,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but can be differentiated by the following characters: anal tube with ventral margin inflated to fin-like apex (
<figureCitation box="[891,959,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[944,959,871,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E), larger than 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1228,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Hilavrita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxeta">
<emphasis box="[1124,1228,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">H. saxeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; aedeagus with an ear-like lateral lobe (LL) near ventral apex (
<figureCitation box="[643,711,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,711,907,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" box="[199,679,942,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,942,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Description.</emphasis>
Size. Body length 
<quantity box="[558,675,942,967]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="8.0">8–9.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Coloration. General color light green to whitish grey; eyes fuscous; ocelli very pale white; clypeus yellow; legs brownish yellow, tibia and tarsus slightly darker; tegminal margin slightly orange.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Head. Head (
<figureCitation box="[358,435,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[420,435,1051,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[471,485,1051,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
A) about 
<number box="[603,638,1051,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="3.8">3.8</number>
times broader than long, narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely pointed, lateral margins slightly ridged. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[824,907,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs. 
<number box="[892,907,1087,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[942,956,1087,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
A) in form of hourglass, anterior margin concaved, partly concealed beneath anterior margin of pronotum. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[980,1053,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[1038,1053,1123,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">
<date box="[1038,1053,1123,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">2</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I, 
<number box="[1077,1092,1123,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
B) convex, slightly wider than long, lateral margin convex, strongly carinate, with median longitudinal carina almost full length of frons. Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[215,230,1195,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">
<date box="[215,230,1195,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">2</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I, 
<number box="[253,268,1195,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
B) without carina. Rostrum long, extending to meta-trochanter. Antennal segment I ring-like, segment II about three times longer than segment I (
<figureCitation box="[609,678,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[662,678,1231,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Thorax. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[418,489,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[474,489,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[519,534,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
A, 
<number box="[567,583,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
C): anterior margin convex, posterior margin concave. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1342,1413,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[1398,1413,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[151,167,1303,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
A): anterior margin convex, three longitudinal obscure carinae. Metatibia with six or seven spines apically, basal metatarsal segment with six or seven spines apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[304,376,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[217,1366,497,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1379,489,1848]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Herbiflata species. (A – C) left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E – H) head and thorax, dorsal view; (I – L) head, frontal view; (M – P) head and thorax, left lateral view; (A, E, I, M) H. chromata sp. nov.; (B, F, J, N) H. sacra sp. nov.; (C, G, K, O) H. saxeta sp. nov.; (D, H, L, P) H. xizangensis. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259805/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[362,376,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[411,425,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
D) length 
<quantity box="[540,677,1374,1399]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="7.5">7.5–8.5 mm</quantity>
, width between costal margin and apex of clavus 
<quantity box="[1241,1359,1374,1399]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.0">4–4.5 mm</quantity>
; costal margin convex, apical margin rounded to apex of clavus; postclaval sutural margin convex; costal membrane about 
<number box="[151,186,1447,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="1.3">1.3</number>
times wider than costal cell at bulla (
<figureCitation box="[641,714,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[698,714,1447,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D); costal cell without transverse veinlets; ScP+R stem short, ScP+RA not forked, 
<collectingCountry box="[396,430,1483,1506]" name="Poland" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">RP</collectingCountry>
forked slightly apicad of MP fork; MP forked apicad bulla, branch MP 
<number box="[1270,1275,1497,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1285,1294,1497,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
forked near midlength of tegmen, MP 
<number box="[451,458,1536,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[467,475,1536,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
forked slightly before MP 
<number box="[788,793,1536,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[804,813,1536,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
fork; CuA forked at midlength of CuP, CuA 
<number box="[1344,1352,1536,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="1.0">1</number>
forked apicad of MP 
<number box="[307,314,1575,1589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[323,331,1575,1589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
fork, CuA 
<number box="[452,460,1575,1589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
not forked, CuP about 
<number box="[734,783,1560,1585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="0.54">0.54</number>
length of tegmen, Pcu and A 
<number box="[1126,1134,1575,1589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="1.0">1</number>
fused in apical portion of clavus; m-cua present middle of CuP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Male terminalia. Male anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[570,638,1635,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[622,638,1635,1659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E): ventral margin inflated to fin-like apex, apical margin truncate, anus placed near apex of anal tube. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[622,692,1671,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[678,692,1671,1695]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E) ring-like, slightly higher than wide, anterior margin concave, posterior margin straight, ventral margin much longer than dorsal margin. Genital style (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1294,1707,1732]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[1280,1294,1707,1731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E) elongate, posterior margin projected upward. Phallic complex (
<figureCitation box="[757,825,1743,1768]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[811,825,1743,1767]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E) arched, periandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1171,1743,1768]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[1157,1171,1743,1767]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
G) closed basally, open apically, dorsally with membranous lobe; ventral part with an apical pointed process; lateral lobe with one long process ventrad, lateral emargination deeply concave. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[884,950,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[936,950,1815,1839]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F) bipartite, dorsal part of apex with a wide cephalad process and lateral portion with sharply raised carina, small hooked process (HP) beneath wide process, ventral part of apex pointed, with dorsal lobe (DL) and ear-like lateral lobe (LL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,798,2020]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Female terminalia. Female anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[666,736,1923,1948]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Figs 
<number box="[722,736,1923,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H–I) ovate in dorsal view, apical margin obtusely convex; anal pore situated near middle, paraproct very short, about 
<number box="[758,793,1959,1983]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="0.2">0.2</number>
times as long as anal segment. Gonoplac, in lateral view, narrowly rounded apically, dorsal margin concave medially; disc flat, bearing small teeth in upper and posterior part, posterior margin with long seate (
<figureCitation box="[584,652,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[637,652,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="271" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Gonapophysis IX narrow and small, lateral field flat, membranous near apex (
<figureCitation box="[278,347,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,347,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="271" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Endogonocoxal process narrowly foliate, with apex cuspidal (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1167,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1167,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="271" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Anterior connective laminae of gonapophysis VIII narrow, tapering apicad, apex saw-like, with three teeth along dorsal margin at apex, and ventral margin with one small tooth near apex (
<figureCitation box="[728,795,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,382,1724]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,373,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herbiflata chromata sp. nov. (A) head and thorax, dorsal view; (B) head, frontal view; (C) head and thorax, left lateral view; (D) tegmen; (E) male terminalia, left lateral view; (F) aedeagus, left lateral view; (G) periandrium, left lateral view; (H) female terminalia, left lateral view; (I) female anal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviations: HPhooked process; DL—dorsal lobe; LL—lateral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="271">
Fig. 
<number box="[780,795,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="271" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Sternum VII with posterior margin distinctly concave at middle.
</paragraph>
